A 12-year-old girl confirmed infected with COVID-19 has died in Belgium, health officials said Tuesday. The young age of the fatality “is a very rare occurrence,” said a government spokesman, Dr Emmanuel Andre, adding that her death “shook us”. It was the first death of a child in the coronavirus crisis gripping Belgium, which has now recorded a total 705 deaths from the disease it causes, according to the latest official toll. (AFP) Teacher confirmed as first French coronavirus death First case of coronavirus confirmed in Jordan, Rome, Andorra Coronavirus kills Iran supreme leader adviser